@startuml Key Data Structures
!theme plain
title Nova Firmware Key Data Structures\nShared State and Module Interfaces

class "shared_state_t" as State {
  **Global State (protected by g_state_mutex)**
  --
  +app_state_t state
  +uint16_t target_rpm
  +bool motor_running
  +bool motor_forward
  +bool motor_fault
  +uint16_t depth_mm
  +tap_mode_t tap_mode
  +bool menu_active
  +uint32_t motor_queue_overflows
  --
  **Thread Safety:**
  [SHARED_STATE:g_state_mutex]
  Access via STATE_LOCK()/STATE_UNLOCK()
}

class "motor_status_t" as MotorStatus {
  **Motor Controller Status (motor.c)**
  --
  +motor_state_t state
  +uint16_t raw_flags
  +uint16_t speed_rpm
  +uint16_t load_percent
  +uint16_t vibration
  +uint16_t temperature
  +uint16_t target_speed
  +uint8_t retry_count
  +uint32_t last_update_ms
  +bool fault, overload, jam_detected
  +bool rps_error, pfc_fault
  +bool voltage_error, overheat
  --
  **Thread Safety:**
  [SHARED_STATE:g_motor_mutex]
  Updated by motor task only
}

class "diagnostics_t" as Diag {
  **System Diagnostics (Phase 7)**
  --
  +uint32_t uart_tx_timeouts
  +uint32_t uart_rx_timeouts
  +uint32_t uart_bytes_sent
  +uint32_t uart_bytes_received
  +uint32_t event_queue_overflows
  +uint32_t motor_queue_overflows
  +uint16_t event_queue_peak
  +uint16_t motor_queue_peak
  +uint32_t protocol_checksum_errors
  +uint32_t protocol_frame_errors
  +uint32_t protocol_timeout_errors
  +uint32_t protocol_commands_sent
  +uint32_t protocol_queries_sent
  +uint32_t protocol_retries
  +uint32_t mcb_comm_failures
  +uint32_t mcb_comm_success
  +uint32_t mcb_total_queries
  +uint32_t boot_timestamp_ms
  +uint32_t watchdog_refresh_count
  --
  **Thread Safety:**
  [MODULE_LOCAL]
  Incremented from various contexts
}

class "motor_cmd_t" as MotorCmd {
  **Motor Command (queue message)**
  --
  +motor_cmd_type_t cmd
  +int16_t param
  --
  Sent via g_motor_cmd_queue
  From: Main, Tapping tasks
  To: Motor task
}

class "event_type_t" as Event {
  **UI Event (enum)**
  --
  EVT_BTN_F1..F4
  EVT_BTN_ENCODER
  EVT_ENC_CW, EVT_ENC_CCW
  EVT_MOTOR_FAULT
  EVT_JAM_DETECTED
  EVT_TEMP_WARNING
  EVT_OVERHEAT
  EVT_BOOT_COMPLETE
  --
  Sent via g_event_queue
  From: UI, Motor, Tapping tasks
  To: Main task
}

class "jam_status_t" as JamStatus {
  **Jam Detection Status (Phase 2.3)**
  --
  +jam_type_t type
  +uint32_t timestamp
  +uint16_t duration_ms
  +bool acknowledged
  --
  **jam_type_t:**
  JAM_NONE
  JAM_STARTUP_TIMEOUT
  JAM_STALL_DETECTED
  JAM_COMM_TIMEOUT
  JAM_LOAD_SUSTAINED (Phase 2.3)
  JAM_LOAD_SPIKE (Phase 2.3)
}

class "crash_dump_t" as Crash {
  **Crash Dump (crash_dump.c)**
  --
  +crash_type_t type
  +uint32_t timestamp
  +uint32_t pc, lr, psr
  +char task_name[16]
  +uint16_t checksum
  --
  **Phase 1.3: String safety**
  task_name uses strncpy()
  + null termination
}

class "settings_t" as Settings {
  **User Settings (EEPROM/Flash)**
  --
  +speed_settings_t speed
  +tapping_settings_t tapping
  +sensor_settings_t sensor
  +power_settings_t power
  +motor_settings_t motor
  +depth_settings_t depth
  --
  Loaded at boot
  Persisted to EEPROM
}

' Relationships
State "1" *-- "1" Event : g_event_queue
State "1" *-- "1" MotorCmd : g_motor_cmd_queue
MotorStatus "1" -- "1" State : motor status → g_state
JamStatus "1" -- "1" State : jam → EVT_JAM_DETECTED
Diag "1" -- "1" State : tracks queue_overflows
Settings "1" -- "1" State : loaded into g_state

note right of State
  **Phase 5: Thread Safety**

  All static variables classified:
  • [TASK_LOCAL] - Single task only
  • [MODULE_LOCAL] - Module internal
  • [SHARED_STATE:mutex] - Protected

  g_state is the main shared state
  protected by g_state_mutex
end note

note right of Diag
  **Phase 7: Comprehensive Tracking**

  Monitors ALL safety features:
  • UART timeouts (Phase 1.1)
  • Queue overflows (Phase 1.2)
  • Protocol errors (Phase 6)
  • MCB communication health
  • System performance

  Access via:
  diagnostics_get() → read-only
  diagnostics_*() → increment counters
end note

note bottom
  **Memory Layout:**

  Queues: Static allocation (no malloc)
  • g_event_queue: 32 × 4 bytes = 128 bytes
  • g_motor_cmd_queue: 16 × 8 bytes = 128 bytes

  Mutexes: Static allocation
  • g_state_mutex
  • g_motor_mutex
  • g_uart_mutex

  Total Static RAM: ~11,156 bytes (22.7% of 48KB)
  Free Stack Space: Monitored via STACK command
end note

@enduml
